Rating: 4
Made this recipe "as is" and it was terrific. Now for all those changes - that is what is great about this. You can make it your own Scampi as you wish. Lemon? Sure go ahead it's another riff on the classic. More red pepper? Have at it and what about trying a little minced Serrano or jalapeño chile. You may end up with something you'd find in Veracruz or the Southwest. Personally I used "jumbo" shrimp. Although there is no FDA rule about what can be called "jumbo" mine were 16-20 to a pound. And if you, the "chef" in your home" likes it, chances are very good that your family and friends will love it. Try it over rice with a sprinkling of cilantro, or over saffron rice for a change from pasta.

