I usually don't write reviews if I change anything in a recipe because it drives me crazy when people change a recipe, then say it wasn't any good. But I changed this one and it still tasted great! My version was a more "country" style~ I used penne for the pasta, and I didn't run the garlic through a press. Instead I used a combination of chopped garlic and chopped desensitized garlic. I used a Pinot Grigio for the wine- not very dry but was perfect. I added broccoli when I added the shrimp to the sauce, and it was a great addition. I forgot the salt- didn't miss it! Next time I may add roasted garlic and some other veggies. This is definitely a dish I will continue to make.

