I've made this countless times and it's always a hit. We make two adjustments, one for taste and one for texture. We reduce the black pepper to 1/4 tsp and reduce the butter to 3 tbs. My daughter preps the other ingredients while I clean the shrimp and the pasta water is heating. I start cooking when I drop the pasta and it all comes out at the same time. Drying the cooked pasta in its drained pan helps all the flavors adhere to the pasta. Good food and a great time. Capers...hmmm sounds yummy!

