This is such a simple and enjoyable recipe to make. I have followed these directions four times now and have finally found what I think is a slightly better adjustment. I found it far too buttery initially, and that's not to say that I worry about fat or whatnot because if it tastes good, it's good, but this amount of butter didn't really taste so good to me, so I cut it down to about two teaspoons. There's a delicate balance between the butter and the garlic and the lightness of the shrimp and the fineness of the angel hair pasta, so less butter is more better. And, of course, you should really top with lots of parmeggiano.

