Great recipe, very easy. Loved the pepper flakes, was kinda apprehensive to add them, but I thought it made the dish, yet not too spicy. I agree, restaurant quality, especially since a lot of restaurants don't do scampi that well. I even used frozen, cooked shrimp. I soaked them in cold water for 15 minutes, then sauteed them only slightly...didn't want to overcook since they were already cooked. I just heated them on both sides (they were still cold in the middle but not frozen), then when I threw them back into the pan at the end, I kept them in a minute or two to heat them the rest of the way through. Will definitely make this again.

