This was very easy, delicious and smells great because of all the garlic, which I increased to 6 large cloves. Take shrimp out of pan as soon as they turn opaque to avoid them getting tough.

Rating: 4
I made this tonight exactly as indicated with the only exceptions of reducing salt to 1/2 tsp and adding one diced (seeds removed) tomato with the garlic. Amazing. Two keys to this recipe: 1) do not overcook the shrimp by 2) keeping the temperature to medium/medium high and removing shrimp once middle of shrimp are almost (but not completely) white. By turning each shrimp as the recipe calls for rather than tossing them in the skillet, you will get consistency with the cooked shrimp. My wife loved this dish as did I and we considered it "restaurant quality." Next time, I will reduce salt to 1/4 tsp as we are salt sensitive. Will make again and again. Great dish for company as well.

Rating: 3
Really easy to make. I added some sauteed broccoli and that was nice. For presentation, I would remove the shrimp from the sauce, toss the pasta, plate it, and then put the shrimp on top. On a side note, I found this recipe on the iPhone application while in the grocery store! What a lifesaver that is!

