I made this with 3 tablespoons of butter instead of 5 since I was afraid the 5 would be too oily and it was still great. Left of the hot pepper flakes since my sons don't like them. Great dish and except for peeling the shrimp, very easy.

Rating: 4
This was a great recipe and very simple to make. We did end up adding in scallions at the very end to the hot dish. The butter wine sauce, although seemed extremely rich, went over very well once the pasta was all mixed in. I thought it would be too salty (we used salted butter) but it actually needed a bit more salt once the sauce was distributed though the pasta. I had no problems at all with this recipe. Absolutely delicious. I was careful when cooking the shrimp in the hot olive oil not to heat the oil too hot because olive oil tends to be sensitive to higher heat. 2 minutes a side for the shrimp and it's was a winner at a lower oil temp. Plus, we made so much... I think we quadrupled the recipe to have enough for 10 people. We did have some leftovers.

