Rating: 4
For those who cooked this recipe and found it flavorless, I wonder whether they followed the recipe literally? We made this recipe tonight, adding two more garlic cloves and some lemon as suggested by many others. The dish blew our heads open with the most garlicky flavor ever. (Not a problem, since my boyfriend and I love garlic and we know each other well ;-)) The recipe calls for the garlic to be forced through a garlic press. This brings out the juice and garlic flavor. I'm sure if you chopped the garlic it would turn out completely differently. Next time, we'll make it with the original amount of garlic, plus 6-8 thin lemon slices, added near the end. The dish a simple and quick carbo-loading delight.

