Rating: 4
I used Ecco Domini Pinot Grigio for the wine and it gave the dish a lovely taste. I used baby scallops and small shrimp. I marinated them in wine, juice of half a lemon, salt and pepper for about 30 min. while I prepped the veggies. (I used the rest of the lemon juice in the sauce at the end to finish it off. I used Linguini Fini (Barilla) for the pasta and it was wonderful. Delicate enough for the sauce but not too fine for the veggies. I felt Capellini would have been too delicate. For veggies I used 1/2 each of a zucchini and yellow squash, mushrooms, and asparagus. To start I sauteed the shrimp/scallops with marinade and all in olive oil along with two chopped garlic cloves (I don't like a lot of garlic) and some red pepper flakes. Set them aside and added them back in. They turned out tough, so next time I will begin with the veggies and add the meat at the very end of the cooking time. I used chicken stock and plenty of wine (at least a cup of each) as liquid for the sauce. Next time I will try adding a bit of clam juice and maybe some clams themselves instead of the shrimp/scallops or even in addition to them. I made about 1.5 lbs of pasta. I could have made two and had plenty of goodies in it although I may have needed more chicken broth or the clam juice for a bit more sauce. I also added a heaping Tbsp. of margarine but would like to try leaving it out next time to cut the fat content as I don't feel it really needs it. I topped it off with parmesan and some fresh flat leaf parsley. This was delicious. My kids loved it and I'll definitely be making this again.

