Very good and very easy. I took an extra step and sauteed a 1/2 lb of mushrooms first, and added those to the cooked shrimp, as another reviewer had suggested. We thought it tasted great, but it wasn't until after dinner that I realized I forgot to add the parsley! So with it, I think it would have been even tastier, and very nice looking. I also added a good squeeze of fresh lemon, as recommended by a different reviewer. And as for the heat: I used a full 1/2t of crushed red pepper, but it was the red pepper that our favorite pizza place uses, not the crushed red pepper sold in the spice aisle, which tends to be much hotter. We wouldn't have been able to tolerate that quantity of red pepper flakes. ALSO, I only used 1/2 lb of pasta (for two of us) and didn't need any of the reserved pasta water. GREAT recipe, and I think we'll try adding fresh baby spinach leaves next time (what a great idea).

Rating: 4
